<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41001d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41001d">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41001d"> 1(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> by special / remainder</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Lord Roberts&apos; only son had been killed in action in the South African War, and Lord Rhondda had no son. The peerages granted to them were accordingly limited to descend <mark>by special remainder</mark> in default of male issue to their &ldquo;daughters and the heirs male of their bodies&rdquo; respectively. <small> Maud I. Crofts, <a name="MICW" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MICW"><cite title="source">Women under English Law</cite></a>, 1st ed. (1925) 2n</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
